FBIS3-8195 "dreeu044_d_94003" FBIS-EEU-94-044 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Mar 1994 SLOVAKIA Roman Kovac Expelled LD0503210494 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 2000 GMT 5 Mar 94 LD0503210494 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network Language: Czech Article Type:BFN [Text] Deputy Arpad Matejka has become the new chairman of the Republican Council of the Movement for a Democratic Slovakia [HZDS]. He is replacing Roman Kovac, who has been expelled from the HZDS. This decision was made by the leadership of the ruling movement in Trnava today. Vladimir Meciar indicated that he was striving to add another party to the government coalition. However, he did not say which party he had in mind.
